Instructions:

  1. Login

    • POST request /user/login

    • Save headers.cookies for subsequent requests.

  2. Check if job is in Scout

    • GET request /job/jobs?conditions=ISBN13%3d{isbn}
    • Job record will be returned as response if the title exists

        • Job is in Ready to Order

      1. Check if component exists in Job record.PartsList
      2. If component exists you can delete the component.
      3. PATCH request /page/page/{JobID}
        4. 
{
            
"type": "delete",
        
"ordinal": "1",
        
"count": "288",
        
"part": "text",
        
}
        note: PartPages.{component} from the Job record will give you the current pagecount for your components. If you are deleting an entire component the ordinal position should be 1 in the body request
      4. Once component has been deleted or if that component didn't exist you can move the job to Corrections.
        POST request /job/job/{JobID}/preflyt?process=TEP2Scout

        note: When the job moves from Ready to Order to Corrections the JobID will change. please re-query
        GET request /job/jobs?conditions=ISBN13%3d{isbn} to pickup the new JobID for subsequent queries. The Ready to Order jobs have a JobID with a "TEP" prefix and Correction jobs have a JobID with a "TS" prefix. These prefixes also help determining if a job is in Ready to Order or Corrections accounts.

      5. Proceed to Bulk Upload Request

        Job is in Corrections

      1. Check if component exists in Job record.PartsList
      2. If component exists you can delete the component.
      3. Delete component using same method as Step 3 in "Job is in Ready to Order"
      4. Proceed to Bulk Upload Request

        Job does not exist in Scout

      1. Proceed to Bulk Upload Request

  3. Bulk Upload Request

    • GET request /job/bulkupload

    • Upload to S3 to the S3Folder using AccessKeyID and SecretAccessKey Credentials.
      Save BulkID from BulkUploadRecord for subsequent requests

  4. Bulk Upload Complete

    • POST request /job/bulkcomplete?bulkid={BulkID}

(Bulk_Request) Create a new instance for bulk upload

GET /job/bulkupload

This operation provides an interface for initiating bulk upload. The API will return the Amazon AWS S3 location and time limited, write only access credentials needed to upload one or bulk jobs into the LSCScout system. Once provided with the AWS location, one or more files will be uploaded into the system via tools of the users choice (s3cmd, http, amazon console). When these uploads are complete, the user must POST the bulk metadata to /job/bulkcomplete, with the bulkid (returned in BulkUploadRecord) in the request.
sessiontoken

The dynamic session token used to prevent cross tab scripting. This token may also be provided in any of the JSON body requests for PUT/POST/PATCH methods.

(Bulk_Request) Notify that a bulk request is complete

POST /job/bulkcomplete

This API notifies the LSCScout system that a bulk upload request is complete so processing can begin. The API requires the bulkid that is returned from the bulkupload request and the post data for the bulk jobs metadata csv (which is the concatinated contents of the individual CSV files in each uploaded zip. This will allow the processing to begin with the files uploaded.

(Page_Create) Create a new page block

POST /page/page/{jobid}

This operation will allow a user to upload and insert one or more pages into the requested part at the pages specified. The part defaults to body and page ordinal defaults to zero.

application/json application/pdf

If application/json is passed this provides page information. If application/pdf is passed, the page information is extracted from the Job record and information within the PDF.

PageUpdateItem

PageUpdateItem: object

type: string , x ∈ { copy , delete , move , refolio , setvalue }

Type of page operation:

  • copy - Copy a page from an ordinal/part to another ordinal/part.
  • delete - Delete a page from a part
  • move - Move a page from one ordinal/part to another ordinal/part
  • refolio - Sequential change to page Folio for a page range
  • setvalue - Set page key/value pair for a range of pages
ordinal: number

Starting page ordinal

count: number

Count of consecutive page to operate on (defaults to 1)

part: string

The job part this operation applies to

destination: number

Destination of a move or copy (not used for delete)

destinationpart: string

The job part for the destination of this operation

folio: string

(required for refolio operation) new starting folio

tag: string

(required for setvalue) Dot separated list of tag names

value: object

(required for setvalue) New value for tag
